Tropical Storm Philippe, churning
across open Atlantic waters southeast of  Bermuda , is expected to
grow into a hurricane tomorrow, the National Hurricane Center
said.  Philippe, 720 miles (1,160 kilometers) from Bermuda, is
moving west at 10 miles per hour with 65 mph winds, the Miami-
based center said in a 5 a.m. website  advisory . Itâ€™s forecast to
turn to the northwest tomorrow, the NHC said.  Philippe is the 16th named storm in the  Atlantic hurricane
season  that runs from June through November.  To contact the reporter on this story:
